                "CHEF DE PARTIE\nAPPLY NOW \u00bb\nLocation: Graceland, ZA\nCompany: Peermont Global (Pty) Ltd\n \nJob Purpose\nTo assist the Jnr Sous/ Sous chef with the supervision, control, co-ordination of kitchen personal, whilst maintaining the highest possible standard of food preparation and service.\n \nQualifications\nFormal Qualifications\nMinimum:\nMatric\nDegree/Diploma in Hospitality Management or equivalent\n \nMinimum Requirements\nPrior Experience\nMinimum:\n2-3 years' experience in similar position\nMicrosoft Office, outlook, materials control\n \nMain Responsibilities\nCoordinate and execute mise en place\nManage and adhere to hygiene, health, and safety\nFinancial management of the department\nExecute staff training and development\nEnsure proper departmental planning\n \nAPPLY NOW \u00bb",
                " \n \n \n \nPROMOTIONS & EVENTS MANAGER\nAPPLY NOW \u00bb\nLocation: Graceland, ZA\nCompany: Peermont Global (Pty) Ltd\n \nJob Purpose\nTo effectively plan, manage and execute the Resort promotions and events (including Hotel, Casino and Convention areas) in accordance with the Peermont Group standard. To target relevant markets, deliver superior revenue results within budget, and create an exciting and engaging environment for resort guests.\n \nQualifications\nGrade12\nRelevant Degree or Diploma\n \nMinimum Requirements\nA proven track record in a similar role\nAt least 5 years\u2019 experience in a Marketing management role, preferably in the gaming, hospitality, or entertainment industry\nExcellent communication and interpersonal skills\nBe proficient in MS Office 365, including above average computer and presentation skills\nAbility to interact with people at all levels\nInnovation and creativity, with attention to detail is a key attribute of this position.\nGood organisational and administrative skills\nBe a team player with a can-do attitude\nBe emotionally mature in working under pressure\nBe analytical thinker\nBe prepared to do shift work\nOperationally required to work in a smoking environment.\nWill be required to obtain a Gaming Board License from the relevant provincial gaming board\n \nMain Responsibilities\nDevelop and implement casino and hospitality promotions, competitions, and activations for the relevant Peermont Resort. Excellence in promotional execution is a key metric of the role and requires:\nIdentified and sound business objectives\n Business Intelligence integration and reporting\nInvolvement from Management and sound marketing principle\nPlan a relevant and financially viable entertainment calendar aimed at relevant target markets with the aim of:\nEffectively increasing footfall on complex\nEnsuring effective conversion strategies to increase gaming (this also applies to music concerts, shows, entertainment, family holiday programmes, sporting events, festivals etc.)\nImplement and manage the Peermont Winners Circle Rewards Programme, including:\ncollateral, awareness, promotional strategies, events and entertainment strategies, local partnerships, customer relationship management and fulfilment.\nBe involved and champion communication of CSI initiatives and related Public Relations (including social media).\n \nAPPLY NOW \u00bb\n \n \n \n \n ",
                "MAINTENANCE MANAGER\nAPPLY NOW \u00bb\nLocation: Mmabatho Palms, ZA\nCompany: Peermont Global (Pty) Ltd\n \nJob Purpose\nLead the Maintenance function in providing both a reactive and proactive, multi-skilled maintenance service on all operational equipment and facilities infrastructure. Responsible for planned scheduling creation and overseeing the adherence and timely completion of work carried out.\n \nQualifications\nMatric\nTechnical qualifications/Apprenticeship\nRelevant manufacturing/engineering degree is preferred.\n \nMinimum Requirements\n5 years artisan experience\n5 years Management/Supervisory experience\n Previous technical and maintenance experience in a Casino/Hotel environment will be an advantage\n Excellent planning and organizational skills\nGood financial acumen\nGood Interpersonal Skills\n Preference will be given to affirmative action candidates\n \nMain Responsibilities\nMaintenance of the reticulation services, water drainage, electricity, gas and air conditioning\nGeneral maintenance throughout the complex\nPlanned preventative maintenance\nMaintenance on HVAC and refrigeration\nMonitor and co-ordinate all services performed by contractors on site\nConduct inspections of building and grounds to ensure complex complies with building regulations and in line with occupational, Health and Safety Act\nAttend to breakdowns\nStaff supervision, direction and development\nSubmit energy saving initiatives\nBudgeting, analyzing monthly financial statement for the department and cost saving\n Ensure FMS is controlled and regular reports are completed\nParticipate in operations development meetings\nEnsure guest satisfaction by dealing with queries and complaints efficiently\n \nAPPLY NOW \u00bb",
                "HELP DESK SHIFT LEADER\nAPPLY NOW \u00bb\nLocation: Emperors Palace, ZA\nCompany: Peermont Global (Pty) Ltd\n \nJob Purpose\nTo manage the IT Help Desk team in order to provide first line IT technical support and ensure that user issues are dealt with promptly and effectively and to perform implementation, maintenance, support and backup tasks as allocated by Management, adhering to deadlines and quality specifications.\nQualifications\nGrade 12\nA+\nN+\n \nMinimum Requirements\n3 years experience in a hardware / desktop support role\nWorking knowledge of Microsoft Products\nPrinter setup and configuration, network printing\n \nMain Responsibilities\nProvide direction and feedback to the team during shifts.\nManage the process of new Equipment setup and installation by allocating tasks to the resources.\nMonitor and manage equipment spares and stores\nMonitor and evaluate that Backup and Recovery, Infrastructure Monitoring Cabling and Patching is conducted by the team\nManage projects\n \nAPPLY NOW \u00bb"
