                "FINANCIAL PLANNING\nMidrand\n \nSF3-ZA-F-2,SF3-ZA-F-2 / SPEC., FINANCIAL CONTROLLIN\n \nThe Specialist: Controlling will be responsible for the monthly management accounts, profitability steering through business analysis and financial modelling as well as preparing budgets, business cases, forecasts and Long-Range Plan packs.\n \nKey accountabilities of the function\nPreparation and submission of monthly and quarterly results.\nPreparation of monthly management accounts, variance analysis and commentary.\nPreparation of impairment calculations. Review of analysis of data underlying the impairment calculations. Review of RV and credit risk parameters together with the risk department.\nEnsure that FPM data is submitted to AG on a monthly basis.  Review, analyse and advise business lines on FPM results on a monthly basis.\nInterprets and make assumptions about business line results, with regards to actual and forecasts.\nClarification of results and abnormalities with business line managers.\nCo-ordination and preparation of forecast and budgets for submission.\nCost and Interest allocations.\nReview and analysis of submissions by business line and cost centre managers.\nMaintenance of General ledger Structure.\nManage and maintain financial models for the business lines to assist in profit steering.\nManagement accounts \u2013 further development of management accounts in terms of content, preparation and availability.\nControl and reporting of the OPEX budget, including cost per contract, for assigned cost centres.\nPerform advanced data analytics into business line activities to derive trends, measure the outcomes of business cases, as well as highlight the health of key performance indicators such as penetration, retention and retailer support.\nCreation of business intelligence/dashboard to provide near-to-real-time data for business line and executive committee members to use in their daily decision-making processes.\nControl and reporting of headcount.\nPrepare and/or assist with business cases.\nActively create efficiencies through technology and automation to increase accuracy, quality and time to complete mandatory tasks involving financial information.\nAny other task that management may necessitate in reaction to unexpected changes to our environment, greater business needs or to mitigate the vulnerability of the BMW Groups reputation or potential financial loss\nInternal Control systems or ICS - focus on regular monitoring of controls and on testing of controls effectiveness (e.g., performing monthly spot-checks and/or reviewing exception reports); conduct annual process & control review (incl. review / update of process maps / flows and relevant regulations / work instructions)\n \nEducation\nBachelor\u2019s Degree (Accounting/Management Accounting and Statistics); Honours Degree Advantageous\n \nWork experience, Leadership experience\n4-5 Years experience within the financial services industry at a similar job/occupational level.\nAdditional skills: special skills / technical ability etc.\nKnowledge of SAP; MS Office (Advanced Excel); Business Intelligence software (Tableau, PowerBI)\n \n \nLegal entity: BMW Financial Services (South Africa) (Pty) Ltd.\nLocation: Midrand\nJob field: Financial Planning\nJob ID: 116670\n \nAPPLY",
                "Operations Financial Services\n\nSouth Africa\nANALYST: SALES SERVICES\n\nThe incumbent will be responsible for reporting of sales performance, identifying sales trends, preparing proposals, creating and delivering presentations, finding opportunities to digitize internal processes and acting a project manager for IT projects. In addition, the incumbent is required to collaborate in initiatives that will increase sales including loyalty programme, incentives, retailers\u2019 loyalty bonuses.\n \nTasks:\nCompile competitive analysis to support strategic pricing and product forums and for Headquarter.\nEnsuring that Retailer commissions and incentives are paid timeously and are approved and accurately. \nDrive overall management of the dealer incentive programme, dealer enquiries and supplier liaison relating to points allocation & payment processing including registration processes and systems.\nManaging Sign off Process of Engage Points- Bi-monthly /monthly, ensuring on-time payment.\nOversee development of and implementation and integration of new User registration system.\nMaintain and ensure User Registration Systems are running optimally.\nManage external supplier integration of systems security and process reengineering.\nManage users/Dealers access for BMW, MINI, BMW Motorrad, ALPHERA,  and ALPHERA Connect on Common Solution.\nCompile and process Regional Managers Incentives /Internal Commissions on monthly basis.\nTransfer deals between dealers and users before month end to ensure correct unit allocation.\nServe as First Line of Defence (FLOD) Representative is V Division\u2019s liaison between SF-G-4 and V Managers in preparing and delivering FLOD related updates, reviews, etc. \nParticipate as the ICS Champion to drive ICS Risk Processes and facilitate sales and marketing Department with process maps and Procedure Manuals and on ongoing basis ensure updates, reviews and maintenance.\nParticipate in the development and implementation of Marketing and Sales Services\u2019 annual marketing plans. \nRegular interaction with the External Suppliers and Dealer Network for all Sales Support related enquiries.\nManage end-to-end Sales and Marketing Purchasing processes including the timeous raising of purchasing orders, supplier engagement and contractual agreements.\n \nSales Reporting:\nExtract and analyse data for trends and opportunities for the various Sales departments. \nProvide weekly reports and dashboards to support the Regional Managers at retail level.\nProvide weekly reports for EXCO and board meetings.\nBuild standard dashboard that will be used to steer the business and sales.\nProvide reports and data to internal stakeholders for retailer incentive programmes, loyalty programmes and commissions.\n \nProject Management:\nManage allocated IT projects, ensuring delivery on time and within budget.\nAdvise progress to line manager and business managers.\nAdvise on areas of concern within projects and facilitate decision making.\nConsult with external departments to ensure timeous delivery.\nProcess Development:\nImplement new reporting processes to support new or developing sales areas.\nDevelop and implement automated reporting tools to control processes.\nManage and execute processing of incentive programme points and Sprints.\nIdentify and support implementation of automation / efficiencies / process optimization, in or affecting your area of responsibility.\n \nQualifications:\nBachelor\u2019s Degree or equivalent.\n4-6 years\u2019 experience in a similar role within the financial services/motor industry.\nGood Communication skills.\nSystem and processes enhancements\nFluent in business English. \nGood Negotiation skills.\nInterpersonal skills.\nComprehensive knowledge on financial industry and sales field.\nUnderstanding of financial product.\nDetailed-oriented.\nProject Management skills.\nAbility to priorities in a complex environment.\nExperience with Agile working model.\n \nAnalyst: Sales Services\nLegal entity: BMW Financial Services (South Africa) (Pty) Ltd.\nLocation: South Africa\nJob field: Operations Financial Services\nJob ID: 230003UJ\n \nAPPLY"
