                " \nCLAIMS OPERATIONS MANAGER - SOUTH AFRICA\n \nAPPLY\n \nLocations: Johannesburg\nTime type: Full time\nJob requisition id: JR2305369\n \nCLAIMS OPERATIONS MANAGER - SOUTH AFRICA\n \nThe Claims Operations Manager \u2013 South Africa, will report to the EMEA Head of Claims Operations with a matrix to the South Africa Head of Claims. \nThis role will be responsible for claims governance & compliance, process optimization & continuous improvement, strategic execution, project delivery, claims system initiatives and where required, coordinate with TPA management, vendor management, fraud & recovery, business intelligence and Global Quality Assurance.\n ",
                "Key responsibilities for this role include:\nPursue continuous improvement by challenging current processes and ways of working to identify improvement opportunities whilst aligning to broader regional, international and global priorities.   \nSupport in effectively delivering improvement initiatives and project delivery including Global GI Claims Strategic Initiatives, International projects, regional projects, local projects, and IT initiatives ensuring clear prioritization and alignment.\nWork collaboratively with the leadership team across South Africa Claims and Claims IT to identify and implement further opportunity for enhancements to segmentation and our digital capabilities.\nDevelop and manage performance metrics for claims team in collaboration with South Africa Head of Claims, defining operational targets and provide continuous feedback to achieve them.\nMonitor claims team activity to identify trends and opportunities for improvement, including claims initiatives that will improve operational efficiencies, customer journey or indemnity and expense spend improvement.\nCreate an operating reporting framework and report claims performance to stakeholders \u2013 KPI/metric reporting in place monthly/quarterly and distributed to owners for review and analysis.\nSupport effective claims business reporting for South Africa and region. Work with Business Intelligence Team to assist with internal reporting, ensure that accurate and timely reports/changes are maintained as required.\nDrive a strong control framework and lead Claims Governance & Compliance for South Africa Claims working in close collaboration with International Head of Claims Governance and Compliance.\nImplement strong first line controls for key risks identified in South Africa Claims, working collaboratively with Risk Officers, Internal Audit Group and Compliance, to continuously improve. Drive a strong risk management culture in South Africa Claims.\nCoordinate and own (where appropriate) risk event mitigation plans and resolution of internal audit action plans for South Africa Claims.\nCoordinate (where required) and perform governance oversight over key claims compliance requirements (Manager OFR, Duplicate Claims review, Duplicate Claims Payment review, Suspended / Pending Claims Review, Quarterly Reserve Review etc.) and controls (system - LoA reconciliation etc.) and escalate to senior management where required.  \nIn collaboration with South Africa Head of Claims and International Head of Claims Governance and Compliance, develop and maintain South Africa Claims policies, standards, and controls ensuring Claims personnel have knowledge and receive training around AIG policies, standards, and controls.\nEstablish and maintain appropriate means to monitor and accommodate changes in regulatory environment that impact AIG\u2019s compliance obligations.\nPromote various feedback mechanisms ensuring management has the necessary information needed to manage and improve performance.\nCoordinate and ensure timely and appropriate responses are provided to all regulatory, SOX, GQA, internal and external audits.\nWork with South Africa Head of Claims and leadership team across South Africa Claims to ensure that all claim employees with a reserving/settlement/payment has a Letter of Authority (LoA), system authorities are aligned to LoA and has a complete understanding of conditions contained in the LoA and the annexes.\nWork in close partnership with the Claims Operations functional leads - TPA Management, Vendor Management, Business Intelligence, GIS, GRS and GQA to deliver strong performance and oversight for South Africa claims.\nRepresent South Africa Claims in committee/ meetings where appropriate.\nDrive a culture that promotes collaboration, diversity, equity, and inclusion.\n \nKey Qualifications\nThe successful candidate will have proven experience in leading successful operational teams and a demonstrated ability to communicate and influence at varying levels. The individual will also have a proven track record in governance within the Insurance industry ideally within claims.  In addition, she/he will have a proven track record as an exceptionally effective change agent. The candidate will possess a strong business and process mindset and change leadership skills to unify teams around common goals and drive change. \n \nAdditional requirements include:\nHighly motivated and ability to work under own initiative and as part of a team.\nStrong background in operational management and process improvement.\nExpertise in Continuous Improvement Methodologies.\nStrong Compliance, Governance and/or audit, regulatory background. Comprehensive awareness of the Business and Regulatory environment\nExperience in building governance frameworks within a complex organization ideal\nStrong commercial mindset with a proven track record of making sound decisions backed by data\nIdeally experienced in leading client facing teams with a service delivery mindset with knowledge of consumer and commercial claims handling. \nExceptional communication skills including the ability to develop and present clear and concise analysis and recommendations\nProven ability to dissect complex business issues, perform research and analysis, and synthesize conclusions into a value-maximizing strategy\nAbility to connect staff both on an individual level and in large groups; capacity to enforce accountability, cultivate entrepreneurship, and learn the strengths and weaknesses to best leverage skills and nurture talent\n#L1-AIG",
                "We are an Equal Opportunity Employer \nAmerican International Group, Inc., its subsidiaries and affiliates are committed to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and its policies and procedures reflect this commitment. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, gender, gender expression, national origin, veteran status, disability or any other legally protected categories such as sexual orientation. At AIG, we believe that diversity and inclusion are critical to our future and our mission \u2013 creating a foundation for a creative workplace that leads to innovation, growth, and profitability. Through a wide variety of programs and initiatives, we invest in each employee, seeking to ensure that our people are not only respected as individuals, but also truly valued for their unique perspectives.\n \nTo learn more please visit: https://www.aig.com/about-us/diversity-equity-and-inclusion\n \nAIG is committed to working with and providing reasonable accommodations to job applicants and employees with physical or mental disabilities.  If you believe you need a reasonable accommodation in order to search for a job opening or to complete any part of the application or hiring process, please send an email to candidatecare@aig.com.   Reasonable accommodations will be determined on a case-by-case basis.\n \nPreference will be given to previously disadvantaged candidates in line with the company\u2019s Employment Equity Plan. Specific preference will be given to people with disabilities.\n \nFunctional Area: CL - Claims\nEstimated Travel Percentage (%): No Travel\nRelocation Provided: No\nAIG South Africa"
