                " \n \nCONTRACT SPECIALIST\nJob highlights\nGlencore Copper Africa\nJohannesburg, Gauteng, South Africa\nRegional Procurement and Supply Team\nJob IDGCA146\n \nClosing date: 30/11/2023\n \nAPPLY\n\nSupport the Regional Fixed Plant commercial team with the implementation, maintenance and ongoing management of agreed supply and service agreements.\n\nGENERAL ACCOUNTABILITY:\nEnsure implementation, management and maintenance of agreed to supply and service contracts as negotiated by the Regional Fixed Plant strategic sourcing team.\nAssure alignment of regionally agreed contract terms with Global Framework Agreements as may be relevant to the broader Glencore Fixed Plant portfolio.\nAssist the Copper operations team with the verification and implementation of contractual price increases as may be passed on from OEMs/suppliers.\nGive input to tactical and strategic sourcing events as may be executed by the Regional Fixed Plant sourcing team.\nEnsure compliance with agreed to contract terms, deliverables and KPIs.\nSpecific accountabilities \nMonitor contract register within the Regional Fixed Plant portfolio and ensure sourcing projects are executed timeously to replace expiring contracts.\nWill assist and guide the assets/mines about pricing escalations and adjustments as and when submitted by the relevant supplier/s.\nWill be responsible for the verifying of price escalation requests, the negotiating of the requests and the implementation of the approved requests.\nWill review all rate increases, ensure these rates are uploaded timeously and distribute the rates to the relevant sites for record keeping.\nWill be responsible for the review, verification, and implementation of requested contractual amendments and scope variations.\nWill advise Regional Fixed Plant SME\u2019s and Lead on any contractual misconduct or breach of agreed terms and conditions.\nWill ensure effective cost recoupment from OEM\u2019s and suppliers through verification/validation of labor & parts reconciliations, rebates, and discounts.\nEnsuring compliance against contractual performance obligations and deliverables (KPIs).\nAccountable for monitoring and reporting of the commodity spend history and analysis.\nUnderstand market indices and movements as may be necessary to implement contractual price escalations.\nWill ensure new contract terms and conditions as may be negotiated by the Regional Fixed Plant SMEs are aligned with Global Framework Agreements.\nSourcing, analysis and reporting of various contract, spend and market data.\nModelling of costs and scenario analysis.\nFacilitate quarterly / annual Tier 1 Supplier contract reviews.\nDevelopment and maintaining of global and regional supplier KPI reports / dashboards.\nDevelopment of and managing of supplier database for Global and Regional suppliers.\nSupport the Regional Fixed Plant SMEs about the sourcing and procurement of ancillary and material handling equipment, parts and services that support the mining function.\nAssist with ad-hoc unplanned mine site requests related to the Fixed Plant sourcing function.\nAssist Regional Fixed Plant Lead and SMEs as may be required to meet short term site requirements.\nAdvise Regional Fixed Plant team regarding on-site contract requirements as may be relevant to mine sites.\nAssist, consult, and execute on identified continuous improvement initiatives.\nDetermine root causes of problematic process areas and suggest improvements.\nShape unstructured and ambiguous contracts information into a structured format for communication and reporting.\nTracking, updating, and completing of PowerBI dashboards and reports.\n\nThis role will be based in Johannesburg, reporting to the Fixed Plant Pillar Lead. \n\nQUALIFICATIONS:\nBachelor\u2019s Degree / Diploma in Engineering / Business /Commerce/Finance / or Related discipline\n\nWORK EXPERIENCE & SKILL REQUIREMENTS:\n3 \u2013 5 years` experience in supply chain analysis / consulting / planning.\nRelevant experience within a supply chain function.\nExposure to the engineering function as it relates to mining.\nKnowledge or basic understanding of Robotics Process Automation (RPA).\nMulti-tasking and excellent management of time and priorities is essential.\nStrong verbal and written communication skills that work effectively within team and different audiences.\nDemonstrated, well-developed judgment and problem-solving skills.\nPro- active, committed and highly motivated.\nIndependent, flexible, and entrepreneurial.\nTakes initiative and invest energy to resolve queries and take action as needed.\nHigh level of attention to detail and data accuracy.\nA strong solutions and customer/client value focus and ability to work in a global, demanding environment.\nStrong analytical skills and ability to define problems, collects details data, analyse, and interpret results and recommend changes and improvements.\nConsultative engagement approach.\nStrong planning and organizing skills.\nAdapting and responding to change.\nConsider future implications.\n \nAPPLY\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nGROUP ENGINEER \u2013 MOBILE EQUIPMENT\nJob highlights\nGlencore Coal SA\nWitbank\nGroup Services\nJob IDGROUP 2023/51\n \nClosing date23/11/2023\n \nAPPLY\n \nThe incumbent in this role is responsible for assisting with the formulation and delivery of the Group Engineering Strategy. The successful candidate will also take responsibility for engineering issues related to Mobile Equipment as well as support the Complex and Operational Engineering Departments as and when required with strategic initiatives, projects and activities.\n \nKey Responsibilities\nEstablishing Group Engineering Standards, Procedures and Policies.\nDeveloping and Implementing Mobile Equipment Strategies.\nCo-ordination and management of large mobile fleet equipment replacement schedules and long-term procurement initiatives.\nManagement of business risk exposure in terms of equipment performance and critical spares management.\nCoaching and supporting of engineering department at Operational Level.\nIdentifying and implementing business improvement opportunities.\nConducting and managing of project studies.\nLiaising with Industry and academic intuitions.\n \nMinimum Qualifications:\nRelevant degree in Engineering \u2013 B.Sc Eng / B.Eng \u2013 preferably Mechanical.\nGovernment Certificate of Competency.\nRegistered as Pr. Eng or Pr. Cert Eng with ECSA.\nAn additional business or specialist Engineering qualification will be an added advantage.\n \nMinimum Experience:\n10 Years\u2019 experience as an appointed Engineer at Operational level of which at least 2 years in an Engineering Manager position.\nDetailed knowledge of SAP or other Maintenance Management System.\nExtensive knowledge of large open cut mobile equipment.\n \nBehavioural Competencies:\nAbility to apply practical skills and common sense to solve problems and deliver accountabilities.\nApply knowledge, expertise and practical ability to solve problems and deliver accountabilities.\nApply both analysis and intuition to make complex business decisions that drive improvement and results.\nBe conscious of details. Produces consistently high quality and accurate work.\nMaintain high levels of individual and team performance by driving the achievement of goals, targets and financial objectives.\n \nAPPLY\n \n \n \n \n ",
                "MINERAL RIGHTS OFFICER\nJob highlights\nGlencore Coal SA\nWitbank, Mpumalanga, South Africa\nGroup Services\nJob ID: GRS 2023/039\n \nClosing date: 22/11/2023\n \nAPPLY\n \nThe incumbent in this role is responsible for the following components within the Regulatory Affairs Department - Mineral Rights, BBB-EE verification processes and the implementation of the SLP and Mining Charter targets throughout the implementation cycle which includes Governance, Strategy, Performance, Assurance and Improvement, and Communication.\n \nKey Responsibilities\nProviding input into the BBB-EE verification processes to ensure compliance with relevant legislation and improvement of the level/rating.\nAssisting with the compilation, submission, implementation and monitoring of the SLP and Mining Charter targets throughout the implementation cycle which includes Governance, Strategy, Performance, Assurance and Improvement, and communication.\nMaintaining adequate administrative and record keeping systems.\nEngaging with internal stakeholders and keeping up with external developments to ensure that internal processes keep up to ensure legislative compliance and security of tenure.\nEnsuring compliance to all applicable legislated dates for submission and implementation.\n \nMinimum Qualifications\nLaw Degree or equivalent.\nBBB-EE Certificate will be an added advantage.\nDriver\u2019s license (Code EB/08).\n \nMinimum Experience\n3 Years\u2019 experience in the mining, government regulation, legal practice or consulting environment.\n \nBehaviour Competencies:\nAbility to drill into the detail of issues to determine root cause whilst considering urgency, importance, risk and reward factors.\nAbility to inspire and foster commitment, pride and trust amongst team members by taking a democratic approach, seeking and valuing contributions and encouraging collaboration.\nAbility to adhere to rules and regulations, follow instructions and limit risk of non-compliance to the business.\nAbility to maintain high levels of individual and team performance by driving the achievement of goals, s and financial objectives.\n \nAPPLY"
